<font size="3" color="#363636"><b><a href="categories.php?op=newindex&amp;catid=1"><font class="storycat">News</font></a>: The result of a bad seed</b></font><br>
Posted on Sunday, April 28 @ 20:30:41 EDT by <a href="http://www.knightsinitiative.com">webmaster</a></td></tr></table></td></tr></table><br><a href="search.php?query=&amp;topic=1"><img src="images/topics/kilogo.gif" border="0" Alt="news and updates" align="right" hspace="10" vspace="10"></a>
<font size="2" color="#505050"><a href="user.php?op=userinfo&amp;uname=Guriab">Guriab</a> writes "</i>Hiya,
<br />

<br />
Just a few words about what happened today. 
<br />
Today as most of you know, one of our own tried to single handly destroy the proud name of Knights Initiative. We must always keep in the front of our mind and on the tip of our tounges, that all of our actions reflect on our Guild .
<br />

<br />
If you did not know what happened I will tell you , not to gossip but to keep the questions down to a mininum.
<br />

<br />
Stompel  , was asked to do a transfer for a friend of the Knights Initiative. When he recieved the items to transfer he went Anon and ducked out of sight. He refused to return the items, hence making the guild look terrible. All attempts to retrieve the stolen items resulted in a brick wall. He was later found and dismissed from the Knights Initiative.
<br />

<br />
As Co-Leader I took it upon my self to make retrobutions to the victim. I asked for the guild to unite and begin to rain the Ryggor fort and loot the armor that was stolen. You Responded with a tremendous Call To arms.
<br />
At times like this I am saddened yes proud to call Knights Initiative my home and you my family.
<br />

<br />
I alone decided to replace the stolen items, it was my descission and was proud to do it. Our named had been tarnished and I just shined it up a bit. I ask that if you want to donate to me, to help replace the items I gave up, then do this. I would like to start a fund for spells for our caster friends. . This will help boost morral. And make the play a little easier for our younger brother and sisters.
<br />

<br />
I will remember today, that so many of you rallied to the cause for the greater good. We have made a friend in a good guild. It is a bond that will better us in the long run. Remember that We are the Knights Initiative. And so will be forever.
<br />

<br />
In closing, I am very proud of you all. You all have done good today. 
<br />

<br />
Keep up the good fight and safe travels.
<br />
Guriab.
<br />
" 
</font>
